<span class="mntl-sc-block-heading__text"> How to Access Cloud Accounts With ES File Explorer </span>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-41" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
To manage your <a href="https://www.lifewire.com/what-is-cloud-storage-2438541" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1" rel="noopener noreferrer">cloud storage accounts</a> in ES File Explorer:
</p>
<li id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-44" class="comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup"><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup -->
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-45" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
Tap the <strong>cloud</strong> icon in the history bar at the top of the screen (if one is there), or open the main menu and select <strong>Network </strong>&gt;<strong> Cloud Drive</strong>.
</p><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html -->
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-46" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block -->
</li>
<li id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-48" class="comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup"><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup -->
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-49" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
Tap <strong>Log in to Google Drive</strong> to connect to your Google account, or tap <strong>Log in with other cloud drive</strong> to connect to One Drive, Box.net, or Dropbox.
</p><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html -->
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-50" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block -->
</li>
<li id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-52" class="comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup"><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup -->
<p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-53" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
After syncing your accounts, the Cloud Drive screen will show folders representing all your cloud services. Tap the plus sign (<strong>+</strong>) to add additional ones.
</p><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html -->
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-54" class="comp theme-experttiptip mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-callout mntl-sc-block-callout mntl-block" data-tracking-id="mntl-sc-block-callout" data-tracking-container="true">
<div id="mntl-sc-block-callout-body_1-0-6" class="comp mntl-sc-block-callout-body mntl-text-block">
<p>It's possible to copy or move files directly from one cloud service to another from within ES File Explorer.</p></div><!-- end: comp mntl-sc-block-callout-body mntl-text-block -->
</div><!-- end: comp theme-experttiptip mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-callout mntl-sc-block-callout mntl-block -->
<figure id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-55" class="comp mntl-sc-block tech-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-image figure-landscape figure-high-res">
<div class="figure-media">
<div class="img-placeholder" style="padding-bottom:58.9%;">
